==English==

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} {{term|þuma|þūma|lang=ang}}, from {{PG.}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|tūmon-|thick finger}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|tū-|swell}} (compare Latin {{term|tumere|lang=la}}).  Cognate with Dutch {{term|duim|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Daumen|lang=de}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-thumb.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|ʌm}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The short thick [[digit]] of the hand that for humans has the most mobility and can be made to [[oppose]] (moved to touch) all of the other fingers.
# {{computing}} The part of a [[slider]] that may be moved linearly along the slider.

